title: LAPD sends out bomb squad to handle possible ‘explosive device’ in North Hills
text: Los Angeles police sent out a bomb squad to the Southbound 405 Freeway in North Hills Sunday to handle a possible “explosive device,” said LAPD Officer Rosario Herrera, a spokeswoman. The California Highway Patrol requested assistance from the LAPD’s bomb squad, Herrera said. CHP officials issued a SIG alert at about 12:41 p.m. for all lanes of the northbound and southbound 405 Freeway just south of Roscoe Bouelvard. No further information was immediately available. “It’s precautionary and preliminary at this point, so LAPD is on scene and assisting with that,” said CHP Officer Monica Posada.
